  IF  by his torturing  savage foes untraced   The breathle  Captive gain some trackle  glade  Yet hears the war whoop howl along the waste  And dreads the reptile monsters of the shade   The giant reeds that murmur round the flood  Seem to conceal fome hideous form beneath   And every hollow blast that shakes the wood  Speaks to his trembling heart of woe and death  With horror fraught  and desolate dismay  On such a wanderer falls the starle  night   But if  far streaming  a propitious ray Leads to some amicable fort his fight  He hails the beam benign that guides his way  As I  my Harriet  ble  thy friendship  cheering light  
